00:00:06.180 --> 00:00:08.320
This is something called
an error-correcting code.

00:00:08.720 --> 00:00:12.220
So if somehow during transmission
some of the 0s get changed to a 1

00:00:12.220 --> 00:00:15.260
or vice-versa, this code
is able to pick up

00:00:15.260 --> 00:00:16.820
that a mistake has been made.

